Playbook:
* user runs the prune.py script
* for every folder containing .prune:
  * determine max age, 
  * select files satisfying the condition `age > max_age`, 
  * for every selected file:
    * make sure every file exists on the backup server, 
  * prompt the user to confirm pruning of the folder: "Folder "xxx": total size XXX Mb, size to prune YYY Mb. Allow pruning [y]/n?"
  * if confirmed, delete all selected files

